        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-05T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-05T18:00:00-05:00" n="172" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW/4–545: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Secretary of State to the Ambassador in the United
                        Kingdom</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-05T19:00:00-04:00">April 5, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2662. Substance of Department’s 2577, April 3, 8 p.m.<note n="29" xml:id="d172fn29">See footnote 22, <ref target="#pg_216">p. 216</ref>
                    </note> and a copy of your 3405, April 4, noon were communicated to the
                    President. In reply he has sent the following directive: “I do not wish any
                    document or proposal changing the unconditional surrender terms”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
